title: Term Newborn
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains a physical exam finding that represents the number of births of a newborn equal to or greater than 37 completed weeks of gestation.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify  the number of births of a newborn equal to or greater than 37 completed weeks of gestation. Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the "Assessment" category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Include SNOMED CT codes that identify  the number of term births of a newborn equal to or greater than 37 completed weeks of gestation.),(Exclusion Criteria: Exclude codes that do not meet the inclusion criteria.)
